content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1261.41 - Starting and warming-up of aircraft engines restricted to designated areas

State Regulations

Aircraft engines shall be started and warmed-up on an
air terminal only in places designated for such purposes by the manager. No jet
or turbo-prop aircraft engine shall be run-up except in areas authorized by the
manager. Notes
